parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The buildup of oil sludge in the engine can cause premature wear, engine failure, and potentially lead to accidents or strand the driver.
A faulty timing belt can cause engine failure, leading to accidents or strand the driver.
A faulty idle air valve can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or strand the driver.
A faulty valve cover gasket can cause oil leaks, leading to engine failure and potentially accidents or strand the driver.
Sulfur fumes in the vehicle can cause health issues for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Strong sulfur smell inside and outside the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the vehicle to stall or become difficult to shift, leading to accidents or strand the driver.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause extended stopping distances, loss of control, and accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Grinding or squeaking noise when applying brakes
brake pedal goes to the floor
vehicle skids or spins out of control

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake wear can cause extended stopping distances, loss of control, and accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: rear brakes wearing faster than expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause extended stopping distances, loss of control, and accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: vehicle skids or spins out of control
grinding or squeaking noise when applying brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants may not be adequately protected from the impact.
symptoms: Airbags did not deploy in a crash
despite the severity of the impact; occupants sustained injuries or fatalities as a result.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause injuries or distractions while driving, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Airbags deployed without a crash or impact
causing injuries or distractions; airbags deployed at low speeds or in non-collision situations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Airbag deployment issues, such as deploying in ribbons or causing fires, can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbags deployed in an unusual manner
such as in ribbons; airbags caused fires or other secondary hazards.
